lender.occupational_info: A versatile sales professional, executive, and entrepreneur with more than 30 years of experience in a variety of fields, Neil Haboush currently serves as Sales Manager for Level One Data Services in Beaconsfield, Quebec. After one year there, Neil Haboush transferred to Concordia University in Montreal, Canada, where from September 1978 through June 1982 he pursued studies in economics and politics. During this time, Neil Haboush held retail sales positions at a number of clothing stores in and around Montreal, developing his knowledge of the field. After five years advancing through the ranks in the industry, Neil Haboush founded a women’s sportswear company, which he subsequently developed into one of the top private-label manufacturers in the country. In 1998, Neil Haboush closed his sportswear company and entered into a new phase of his career, launching a business consulting firm two years later. Neil Haboush cultivated a specialization in this field, which led to further opportunities over the next decade. Neil Haboush ensures the promotion of his company’s suite of business software to clients across the globe.
